  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2019-05-13",
    "date": "2020-06-08T21:50:25Z",
    "text": "Drug-price Transparency in Communications (DTC) Act\n\nThis bill provides statutory authority for the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services rule titled Medicare and Medicaid Programs; Regulation to Require Drug Pricing Transparency, published on May 10, 2019. The rule requires direct-to-consumer television advertisements for covered drugs and biologics under Medicare and Medicaid to include the list price of a 30-day supply or for a typical course of treatment, if the list price is at least $35 per month. The rule takes effect July 9, 2019."
  },
